DataElement.preferredName: Left Ventricular Ejection Time Measurement Millisecond Number
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the time of ejection of blood from the left ventricle beginning with the opening of the aortic value and ending with aortic value closure, expressed as a number of milliseconds. [Manually-curated]

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: The ejection fraction (or, more correctly, left-ventricular ejection fraction, often abbreviated LVEF) is a measure of how much blood the left ventricle of the heart pumps out with each contraction. With each beat, a normal heart ejects about one-half to two-thirds of the blood in its left chamber.
